No, I said "use the bathroom,"

18:08.901 --> 18:11.165
not squat by the side of the road.

18:29.755 --> 18:34.021
And the weird and wacky talent
this week is...

18:44.703 --> 18:46.068
Congratulations, Wayne.

18:58.784 --> 19:00.046
All yours.

19:01.620 --> 19:03.554
Do you want to play pool, or...

19:03.622 --> 19:05.055
pinball or something?

19:05.124 --> 19:06.216
Nah. We should get going.

19:06.292 --> 19:07.725
Okay.

19:20.306 --> 19:21.568
Turn it down!

19:21.640 --> 19:23.574
Turn it off!

19:29.148 --> 19:30.809
Is this a good show?

19:31.817 --> 19:32.806
Yeah.

19:34.153 --> 19:36.417
I've never seen it before.
Is it new?

19:36.489 --> 19:37.888
Not that new.

19:40.292 --> 19:41.850
I've haven't really seen
much of anything lately

19:41.927 --> 19:46.261
'cause I've been overseas
the past 14 months, and...

19:46.332 --> 19:47.822
you know, I'm in the Army.

19:49.168 --> 19:50.635
But I'm home on leave for 30 days,

19:50.703 --> 19:54.104
so I'm just... I'm hoping to catch up.

19:55.674 --> 19:57.107
I like your jacket.

19:58.611 --> 19:59.543
It's okay.

19:59.612 --> 20:01.011
What's the "I" stand for?

20:03.482 --> 20:04.779
Indiana.

20:04.850 --> 20:08.342
You know, the college and the state

20:08.420 --> 20:10.081
where you're standing right now.

20:12.191 --> 20:16.059
Yeah, you know, I was thinking
of going to college when I get out, but...

20:16.128 --> 20:17.117
Do you like it?

20:17.196 --> 20:19.528
Do you think you could be quiet?

20:23.135 --> 20:25.126
Sure, I can be quiet.

20:25.204 --> 20:26.228
Good.

20:32.878 --> 20:34.311
No way.

20:52.398 --> 20:54.923
You know, I'm limping
because when I was over there,

20:55.000 --> 20:56.365
I got shot in the leg.

20:56.435 --> 20:59.029
That wasn't very smart, was it?

20:59.104 --> 21:00.799
Hey! Hey, hey, hey!

21:07.980 --> 21:10.505
Back off! Back off!

21:10.583 --> 21:11.550
What's wrong with you guys?

21:11.617 --> 21:12.879
Back off!

21:13.886 --> 21:15.319
Calm down.

21:15.387 --> 21:16.854
No, that's right. Be afraid.

21:16.922 --> 21:18.480
No, be very afraid.

21:18.557 --> 21:19.546
Go, go, go!

21:19.625 --> 21:20.557
All right!

21:28.534 --> 21:31.264
Yeah! We won!

21:31.337 --> 21:34.934
Kicked their college asses!

21:35.007 --> 21:38.272
Oh, this girl's crazy.

21:39.511 --> 21:40.671
Yeah.

21:41.880 --> 21:44.371
Just glad I didn't have my weapon.

22:02.201 --> 22:05.762
TV! TV! TV!

22:11.377 --> 22:13.538
- I wish we had some booze.
- Yeah.

22:13.612 --> 22:15.910
Check my bag.

22:15.981 --> 22:18.779
Doctor in Germany gave me
a bottle of schnapps.

22:23.856 --> 22:27.257
And a tough night here at the arena
for the home team.

22:27.326 --> 22:28.918
- Thank you.
- All right.

22:38.103 --> 22:39.070
Not bad.

22:40.372 --> 22:43.170
I mean, what you really want
after a fight is whiskey

22:43.242 --> 22:45.107
'cause it mellows you out.

22:45.177 --> 22:48.408
If you want to get mean, you drink gin,

22:48.480 --> 22:51.449
vodka if you want to zone out,

22:51.517 --> 22:53.542
and you save tequila
for when you want to get crazy.

22:54.720 --> 22:56.210
She didn't need tequila tonight.

23:00.192 --> 23:02.023
Did anybody see a straw around here?

23:03.529 --> 23:04.621
No. Why?

23:04.697 --> 23:06.187
'Cause if you drink through a straw,

23:06.265 --> 23:08.096
it gets you drunker.

23:08.167 --> 23:09.156
That's not true.

23:09.234 --> 23:10.428
Of course it is.

23:10.502 --> 23:11.434
That's ridiculous.

23:13.038 --> 23:14.403
How could that be true?

23:14.473 --> 23:17.465
Well, I don't really know how it works.

23:17.543 --> 23:19.636
It just... It...

23:19.712 --> 23:21.942
It just gets in...
It just goes in faster.

23:22.014 --> 23:24.141
Oh, it's just one of...

23:24.216 --> 23:25.683
one of the mysteries of life?

23:25.751 --> 23:27.719
- Is that what you're saying?
- Uh-huh.

24:04.223 --> 24:05.952
Shit, man.

24:07.426 --> 24:08.654
You okay?

24:09.928 --> 24:12.055
I was...

24:13.599 --> 24:15.430
You know.

24:18.270 --> 24:19.532
Sorry.

24:27.946 --> 24:29.243
Honey, it's me.

24:29.314 --> 24:30.645
You there?

24:30.716 --> 24:32.650
Pick up.

24:34.620 --> 24:36.247
Okay. Well, we got held up a little bit,

24:36.321 --> 24:39.290
but we'll be rolling in
in about two hours or so.

24:46.365 --> 24:48.333
Is that the Mississippi?

24:48.400 --> 24:49.765
That's it.

24:51.737 --> 24:54.706
I always wanted to go
on one of those riverboats.

24:54.773 --> 24:57.367
You know?
Do you think maybe we could stop?

24:57.442 --> 24:58.773
No.

25:26.138 --> 25:27.435
Pat!

25:30.843 --> 25:32.071
Pat!

25:40.552 --> 25:43.282
Honey! I'm home!

25:47.359 --> 25:48.849
Honey?

25:52.231 --> 25:54.062
Sure you got the right house?

25:54.132 --> 25:56.430
Yeah.

25:56.501 --> 25:58.867
Can't believe your own dog
doesn't know you.

25:58.937 --> 26:01.462
We don't have a dog.

26:13.218 --> 26:14.810
Yes, sir.

26:14.887 --> 26:18.379
You have a good life here, Cheaver.

26:32.170 --> 26:33.296
There you are.

26:37.209 --> 26:38.369
Fred.

26:40.245 --> 26:41.371
You're home.

26:48.587 --> 26:50.054
I missed you.

26:51.590 --> 26:55.151
God, I missed you.

26:57.863 --> 26:59.194
Let me get the dog to stop.

27:01.433 --> 27:02.695
Whose dog is that?

27:03.702 --> 27:05.192
Mine.

27:07.339 --> 27:08.499
No, no, no.

27:08.573 --> 27:10.973
Pogo, you come with me.
Yes. You come with me.

27:11.043 --> 27:12.670
Yes. Yes. Yes.

27:12.744 --> 27:14.803
I'm gonna put you in here for a while.

27:14.880 --> 27:17.075
Yes, I know. I'm sorry.

27:17.149 --> 27:18.548
Mommy loves you.

27:22.955 --> 27:23.944
So.

27:26.892 --> 27:28.382
Where you been all my life?

27:29.761 --> 27:31.558
How's your back?

27:31.630 --> 27:34.064
It's fine.

27:34.132 --> 27:35.997
Doesn't matter now.

27:36.068 --> 27:37.592
Scott spent the night at Brad's house.

27:37.669 --> 27:39.899
He should be back soon.

27:39.972 --> 27:41.166
Great.

27:42.341 --> 27:44.070
Where are your friends?

27:45.310 --> 27:46.937
They're out back.

27:48.313 --> 27:49.712
Don't you think we should get them?

27:49.781 --> 27:51.009
Well, sure. Yeah.

27:51.083 --> 27:52.641
- Let 'em in.
- Okay.

27:57.389 --> 27:58.651
Welcome.

28:02.761 --> 28:04.729
Can I get you something to drink?

28:04.796 --> 28:06.127
Yeah.

28:07.532 --> 28:08.999
Do you want one, Fred?

28:09.067 --> 28:10.898
No. Thanks.

28:13.672 --> 28:15.936
Well, I bet you're all glad to be back.

28:16.008 --> 28:17.703
- Yeah.
- Oh, yes, ma'am.

28:19.478 --> 28:21.173
Excuse me for a minute.

28:30.022 --> 28:31.580
Sit down.

28:43.869 --> 28:45.268
So.

28:45.337 --> 28:47.134
How are you?

28:47.205 --> 28:49.400
Fine.

28:49.474 --> 28:52.136
Are you sure?

28:52.210 --> 28:53.142
Is anything wrong?

28:53.211 --> 28:55.202
No. Nothing.

28:56.882 --> 28:58.747
Something's wrong.

28:58.817 --> 29:00.444
I don't see you

29:00.519 --> 29:04.250
for almost two years, and then...

29:06.324 --> 29:07.256
I don't know.

29:07.325 --> 29:09.384
Well...

29:09.461 --> 29:11.053
I don't know, either.

29:13.231 --> 29:17.964
Well, I guess they say that...

29:18.036 --> 29:21.096
you know, that...

29:21.173 --> 29:23.607
it's difficult at first, and...

29:23.675 --> 29:25.973
I'm sorry. I jus... I really am.

29:26.044 --> 29:27.306
I just can't do this.

29:27.379 --> 29:30.473
Everyone told me to wait,
but I don't see the point.

29:31.783 --> 29:33.683
You know me.
I'm no good at pretending.

29:34.686 --> 29:35.812
Pretending about what?

29:37.089 --> 29:38.647
Fred, you're not gonna like this.

29:39.658 --> 29:40.682
Okay.

29:41.993 --> 29:43.290
Okay.

29:46.898 --> 29:48.525
I think I w...

29:50.368 --> 29:52.165
I need a divorce.

29:53.238 --> 29:54.170
What?

29:54.239 --> 29:55.866
I'm sorry.

29:55.941 --> 29:58.910
But to go around pretending
for a week that it's not true,

29:58.977 --> 30:00.569
well, that didn't seem fair to you, either.

30:00.645 --> 30:03.136
Wait a minute...

30:03.215 --> 30:05.877
I come home, and...

30:09.621 --> 30:11.748
Why do...
Why do you want a divorce?

30:11.823 --> 30:14.223
I didn't plan it this way.

30:14.292 --> 30:16.419
It just happened. You were gone.

30:16.495 --> 30:19.464
I'm sorry, but I've moved on.

30:20.799 --> 30:22.027
You gotta be kidding.

30:22.100 --> 30:24.398
I got a new job, and I'm finally happy.

30:25.403 --> 30:26.768
Finally happy? What...

30:26.838 --> 30:28.738
You mean you weren't...
you weren't happy before?

30:28.807 --> 30:30.672
Well, I guess I was. I don't know.

30:30.742 --> 30:32.300
L... I...

30:36.114 --> 30:37.581
You seeing someone else?

30:37.649 --> 30:40.413
- No.
- You can tell me.

30:40.485 --> 30:42.476
I'm not seeing anyone else.

30:42.554 --> 30:44.215
I don't want to see anyone else.

30:44.289 --> 30:46.416
I'm happy being alone.

30:46.491 --> 30:48.857
I want to be alone.

30:48.927 --> 30:52.226
I know that sounds harsh,
but it's the truth.

30:52.297 --> 30:54.265
I am happy.

30:56.501 --> 30:58.401
Without you.

30:59.504 --> 31:01.938
Oh, my God.

31:02.007 --> 31:04.271
This is what makes a guy flip out.

31:05.744 --> 31:06.938
He's gonna strangle her.

31:07.012 --> 31:09.446
If it were you,
you wouldn't strangle her.

31:09.514 --> 31:11.345
Okay.

31:11.416 --> 31:14.044
Shoot her. Whatever.

31:21.593 --> 31:22.617
Hey.

31:22.694 --> 31:24.252
- What's up?
- Hi.

31:24.329 --> 31:26.297
Who are you?

31:26.364 --> 31:28.298
Friends of your dad.

31:28.366 --> 31:30.266
My dad?

31:30.335 --> 31:31.859
- He's...
- Scott.

31:33.838 --> 31:36.068
Dad!

31:36.141 --> 31:39.076
It's good to see you.

31:42.514 --> 31:45.005
Wow! Look at you.

31:48.887 --> 31:50.582
How are you?

31:50.655 --> 31:52.816
I'm good.

31:54.359 --> 31:55.758
How are you?

31:57.462 --> 31:59.259
Just great.

31:59.331 --> 32:00.628
So.

32:00.699 --> 32:02.360
Did Mom tell you?

32:03.435 --> 32:05.266
Yeah.

32:05.337 --> 32:06.463
You surprised?

32:08.573 --> 32:09.767
Yeah.

32:11.543 --> 32:13.704
Can you believe it?

32:13.778 --> 32:15.803
Stanford.

32:15.880 --> 32:17.745
- What?
- I got into Stanford.

32:17.816 --> 32:18.908
What?

32:18.984 --> 32:20.076
Yeah, I got in!

32:20.151 --> 32:21.448
You got into...

32:21.519 --> 32:22.508
I got into Stanford.

32:22.587 --> 32:23.952
Oh, yeah!

32:24.022 --> 32:26.320
Oh, my... Yes! All right!

32:26.391 --> 32:27.790
- I did it.
- I knew you could do it!

32:27.859 --> 32:30.123
Yeah, and I got a scholarship
that'll pay for half the tuition.

32:30.195 --> 32:32.493
- Fantastic.
- And I made six grand working this year.

32:32.564 --> 32:35.727
- Excellent.
- And I need $20,000 to pay for the rest.

32:36.901 --> 32:38.630
That's not so great.

32:38.703 --> 32:41.729
Well, I told him I'm not sure
we can come up with the $20,000.

32:43.808 --> 32:46.003
It's doable.

32:46.077 --> 32:48.910
I'll just get my old job back,
and if we have to,

32:48.980 --> 32:50.845
we'll take a second mortgage
on the house.

32:50.915 --> 32:52.678
We have a second mortgage already.

32:52.751 --> 32:56.881
Well, then we'll sell
the fucking house, all right?

32:56.955 --> 33:00.516
Okay. Well, it took the Schneiders
two years to sell theirs.

33:00.592 --> 33:03.686
I need the money in three weeks
or I lose my place.

33:03.762 --> 33:05.855
I'll get you the money.

33:05.930 --> 33:07.090
I promise.

33:10.568 --> 33:12.331
Can I talk to you?

33:15.106 --> 33:17.802
What are we doing here?
We should be focused on Scott.

33:17.876 --> 33:18.900
I am focused on Scott.

33:18.977 --> 33:22.105
We gotta make sure we can do this for him,
pool our resources, whatever it takes.

33:22.180 --> 33:25.741
Why do you need a divorce right now?
I just don't get it.

33:25.817 --> 33:27.182
I'm sorry, Fred.

33:27.252 --> 33:29.083
But this is what I want to do.

33:29.154 --> 33:30.644
Now, I've had some papers drawn up,

33:30.722 --> 33:34.488
and I just want to stick to the plan.

33:47.305 --> 33:49.535
Listen. We're gonna keep it together.

33:49.607 --> 33:51.404
We're gonna stay calm.

33:51.476 --> 33:55.173
Look, there's no killing yourself
or anyone else, okay?

33:55.246 --> 33:56.508
Hey, you're gonna get through this.

33:56.581 --> 33:57.605
All right? Do you hear me?

34:09.060 --> 34:10.618
This is fine right here.

34:10.695 --> 34:12.253
Here you go.

34:12.330 --> 34:13.422
Cheaver.

34:14.933 --> 34:16.525
Cheaver.

34:16.601 --> 34:18.864
Come on, what's your plan?

34:18.937 --> 34:21.268
I'll take you guys to the airport

34:21.339 --> 34:23.431
and then I'm gonna drive
straight to Salt Lake,

34:23.507 --> 34:24.496
see my brother.

34:26.511 --> 34:28.069
I'm not going back home.

34:28.146 --> 34:29.476
I can tell you that much.

34:29.547 --> 34:31.411
What about your kid?

34:31.483 --> 34:34.782
I'll figure something out.

34:34.853 --> 34:36.547
Your brother should lend you the money.

34:36.621 --> 34:39.987
My brother is in Debtors Anonymous.

34:41.025 --> 34:42.286
Fred?

34:43.795 --> 34:45.786
I thought that was you.
You're back.

34:45.864 --> 34:46.795
Hey, Carl.

34:46.864 --> 34:48.059
- Hi.
- What's up?

34:48.132 --> 34:49.100
How'd it go over there?

34:49.167 --> 34:50.759
Great.

34:50.835 --> 34:52.166
You know, it went great.

34:52.237 --> 34:53.534
Well, we all missed you...

34:53.605 --> 34:54.799
you know, seeing you every day.

34:55.806 --> 34:56.899
Well, I'm coming back.

34:56.975 --> 34:58.499
I'm just gonna take a few days off,

34:58.576 --> 35:00.635
and then it's nose-to-the-grindstone time.

35:00.712 --> 35:02.646
I gotta earn some money.

35:02.714 --> 35:03.772
Yeah.

35:03.848 --> 35:06.749
But, you know,
since Alan's been in charge,

35:06.818 --> 35:08.752
he's just been running
the company into the ground,

35:08.820 --> 35:10.981
and then that lawsuit...
you heard about that.

35:11.055 --> 35:12.522
No.

35:13.525 --> 35:16.392
Already laid off 60 guys, including me.

35:17.929 --> 35:19.920
Shit.

35:19.998 --> 35:22.330
They're shutting down
the whole place next month, so...

35:23.334 --> 35:24.323
Fuck.

35:25.904 --> 35:27.838
Yeah.

35:32.710 --> 35:33.870
Fuck!

35:33.945 --> 35:35.674
- Hey!
- Fuck!

35:35.747 --> 35:36.941
Oh, my goodness.

35:37.015 --> 35:38.277
Fuck!

35:38.349 --> 35:39.907
Okay, there's no need for that.

35:45.757 --> 35:47.281
Take good care of yourself.

35:47.358 --> 35:48.985
Don't drive straight through, okay?

35:49.060 --> 35:50.186
You'll get into a wreck.

35:50.261 --> 35:52.195
Not a bad idea.

35:52.263 --> 35:53.525
What?

35:53.598 --> 35:55.566
Catch a telephone pole going 90.

35:56.668 --> 35:58.135
Collect some life insurance money.

35:58.203 --> 35:59.192
No, no, no.

35:59.270 --> 36:00.498
No, no. Forget that.

36:00.572 --> 36:02.130
'Cause insurance doesn't pay for suicide.

36:02.207 --> 36:04.505
Yeah. Not if it's an accident.

36:04.576 --> 36:07.340
- Enough with the crazy talk, please.
- Yeah.

36:07.412 --> 36:08.640
- You're not being serious...
- I'm kidding, I'm kidding.

36:08.713 --> 36:10.271
- Okay, good. Good.
- It's just a joke.

36:10.348 --> 36:11.872
Yeah, have a nice flight.

36:11.950 --> 36:14.384
And good luck to you.

36:14.452 --> 36:16.511
- All right.
- Drive safe.

36:52.490 --> 36:54.515
- You're on the wrong side, pal.
- Yeah, I know.

36:54.592 --> 36:56.958
You know what?
It's all right, 'cause I'm driving anyway.

36:57.028 --> 36:59.258
What?

36:59.330 --> 37:00.524
We're coming with you.

37:00.598 --> 37:02.088
- No, you're not.
- Yep.

37:02.166 --> 37:03.258
Of course we are.

37:03.334 --> 37:04.631
- No, you're not. You got a...
- Yes.

37:04.702 --> 37:06.169
You have a flight to catch.

37:06.237 --> 37:08.102
We'll fly out of Salt Lake City.

37:08.172 --> 37:09.696
I feel pathetic enough, all right?

37:09.774 --> 37:12.072
Crying don't mean you're pathetic, okay?

37:12.143 --> 37:14.043
I'm fine.

37:14.112 --> 37:15.079
Yeah, you're great.

37:15.146 --> 37:16.443
That's why we're coming with you.

37:16.514 --> 37:18.846
We want to meet your whole family.

37:28.359 --> 37:29.621
This is what you gotta do.

37:29.694 --> 37:33.926
Okay, Cheaver, you gotta get
your finances in order.

37:33.998 --> 37:35.522
All right, you buy a house,

37:35.600 --> 37:37.591
you gotta have an exit plan.

37:37.669 --> 37:39.330
You gotta know how
you're gonna sell it.

37:40.705 --> 37:42.297
You're right.

37:42.373 --> 37:44.841
Hey, easy there, cowboy.

37:46.711 --> 37:48.201
It's for my back.

37:49.881 --> 37:51.075
So what you gotta do

37:51.149 --> 37:54.016
is buy an apartment house, rent it out,

37:54.085 --> 37:55.484
live in the basement for free.

37:55.553 --> 37:58.488
Six months later, you borrow on it
and buy another one.

38:00.758 --> 38:02.623
Am I still living in the basement?

38:02.694 --> 38:04.025
Absolutely.

38:05.029 --> 38:06.155
Take a left.

38:06.230 --> 38:07.959
You can get around this.

38:12.437 --> 38:13.836
Yeah, a man's gotta be indispensable.

38:13.905 --> 38:16.931
You want to move up in the world,
you gotta have skills.

38:17.008 --> 38:18.407
Basic skills.

38:18.476 --> 38:19.909
Yeah, what are your skills?

38:19.978 --> 38:21.502
Leadership.

38:21.579 --> 38:23.171
I'm a leader.

38:23.247 --> 38:24.714
Me, too.

38:24.782 --> 38:26.374
No, you're a private.

38:26.451 --> 38:28.817
That's the opposite of a leader.

38:28.886 --> 38:30.353
You know computer?

38:30.421 --> 38:31.979
Yeah, kinda.

38:32.056 --> 38:35.457
You're at a disadvantage
if you don't master computer skills.

38:36.761 --> 38:40.356
You gotta build on that.

38:40.431 --> 38:42.399
Learn a new word every day, and...

38:42.467 --> 38:44.162
get comfortable with it.

38:46.938 --> 38:49.270
Do you know where you're going here?

38:50.475 --> 38:52.340
I got a sense of it.

38:52.410 --> 38:54.844
I think you might be making your way
around to the east.

38:55.847 --> 38:57.337
No. I'm good.

38:57.415 --> 38:58.882
Cheaver, we going the right wa...

39:02.120 --> 39:03.883
Do you think he's okay?

