01:18:48.370 --> 01:18:51.134
Yeah. Definitely wood.

01:18:51.206 --> 01:18:53.003
So we don't need
these ladies anymore?

01:18:53.075 --> 01:18:55.805
Nope. He's all fixed up.

01:18:55.878 --> 01:18:57.778
He could pound a nail with that thing.

01:18:57.846 --> 01:18:59.677
Pound a nail?

01:18:59.748 --> 01:19:01.272
How do you know that?
Did you touch it?

01:19:01.350 --> 01:19:03.978
No, I didn't have to.
It was just pokin' right into me.

01:19:04.053 --> 01:19:05.782
It's a miracle.

01:19:05.854 --> 01:19:08.345
You are one lucky bastard, T.K.

01:19:19.435 --> 01:19:20.459
You all right?

01:19:20.536 --> 01:19:22.902
Yeah, you don't seem too happy...

01:19:22.971 --> 01:19:24.233
considering.

01:19:24.306 --> 01:19:26.274
I'm all right.

01:19:26.341 --> 01:19:27.569
Yeah, I get to see my girlfriend,

01:19:27.643 --> 01:19:29.907
go back down range
like nothing ever happened.

01:19:29.978 --> 01:19:32.412
T.K., what are you worried about?

01:19:32.481 --> 01:19:33.948
You're on a lucky streak.

01:19:34.016 --> 01:19:35.643
I don't think so.

01:19:35.717 --> 01:19:37.844
I mean, you can only get lucky
for so long, you know?

01:19:37.920 --> 01:19:40.150
Streaks don't last forever,
and I've been burnin' some karma.

01:19:40.222 --> 01:19:42.690
Hey, you can't think that way.

01:19:42.758 --> 01:19:44.749
It's gonna mess your head up,
get you in trouble over there.

01:19:44.827 --> 01:19:48.319
Yeah, you gotta forget about luck.

01:19:48.397 --> 01:19:50.456
I mean, look at Randy.

01:19:50.532 --> 01:19:52.966
Robbing Lucky Jim's, not getting caught.

01:19:53.035 --> 01:19:55.629
That was lucky. Amazing.

01:19:55.704 --> 01:19:59.140
But maybe if he had have got caught,

01:19:59.208 --> 01:20:01.938
he would have gone to jail
and he wouldn't have enlisted,

01:20:02.010 --> 01:20:03.034
and then he might be alive.

01:20:03.112 --> 01:20:05.137
That might be luckier.

01:20:05.214 --> 01:20:07.876
So, you know, just don't think about luck.

01:20:09.852 --> 01:20:12.514
I'm on my third tour.
The odds aren't good.

01:20:15.390 --> 01:20:18.848
Maybe you need to change the odds.

01:20:18.927 --> 01:20:20.417
Maybe you don't go back.

01:20:21.964 --> 01:20:23.124
You can go to Canada.

01:20:23.198 --> 01:20:24.392
Take a break.

01:20:24.466 --> 01:20:27.765
No, I can't go to Canada, man.

01:20:27.836 --> 01:20:29.463
You're a coward if you go to Canada.

01:20:29.538 --> 01:20:32.132
Yeah, but you're a coward that's alive.

01:20:32.207 --> 01:20:34.038
Plus you've done your service.

01:20:34.109 --> 01:20:36.339
Given a lot.
More than most people.

01:20:36.411 --> 01:20:37.537
I can't do it, you know.

01:20:37.613 --> 01:20:39.171
They got shit football in Canada.

01:20:39.248 --> 01:20:40.545
Become a hockey fan.

01:20:40.616 --> 01:20:42.607
No.

01:20:42.684 --> 01:20:44.311
I don't know anyone up there, anyway.

01:20:44.386 --> 01:20:45.478
We'll come visit you.

01:20:45.554 --> 01:20:47.419
I've never been to Canada.

01:20:47.489 --> 01:20:49.150
- Yeah.
- Nah.

01:20:49.224 --> 01:20:51.192
- Yeah.
- I'm good.

01:21:36.205 --> 01:21:38.230
Hey! There's Lucky Jim's.

01:21:41.176 --> 01:21:44.236
Robbing a casino's a ballsy thing to do.

01:21:44.313 --> 01:21:45.940
In a weird way, you gotta admire it.

01:21:46.014 --> 01:21:49.950
You know, he was wearing
a gorilla mask when he did it.

01:21:50.018 --> 01:21:52.077
On Halloween
about three years ago.

01:21:52.154 --> 01:21:55.385
Nobody even looked twice
at a guy running down the street

01:21:55.457 --> 01:21:57.288
wearing a mask and carrying a gun.

01:22:07.636 --> 01:22:09.831
I'm happy for you, T.K.

01:22:09.905 --> 01:22:12.373
You know, you're going home
to your girlfriend,

01:22:12.441 --> 01:22:14.102
and that's gonna be real nice.

01:22:14.176 --> 01:22:16.644
You just treat her right.

01:22:16.712 --> 01:22:17.644
Okay.

01:22:17.713 --> 01:22:19.112
When you get married,

01:22:19.181 --> 01:22:21.672
let me know 'cause I want
to send you something.

01:22:21.750 --> 01:22:23.479
You got lots of celebrating to do.

01:22:23.552 --> 01:22:26.350
You got your bridal shower
and your engagement party...

01:22:26.421 --> 01:22:27.353
All right, Colee.

01:22:27.422 --> 01:22:28.912
- Rehearsal dinner...
- Stop, stop, stop.

01:22:28.991 --> 01:22:31.323
It's gonna be nice.

01:22:31.393 --> 01:22:33.987
Just take care.

01:22:37.933 --> 01:22:39.958
That was a bit forward.

01:22:41.236 --> 01:22:42.635
Good luck at the tables.

01:22:42.704 --> 01:22:43.796
Listen to me.

01:22:43.872 --> 01:22:46.568
You go home,
do what you need to do there.

01:22:46.642 --> 01:22:48.803
If I were you, I'd think twice
about going back.

01:22:50.579 --> 01:22:52.706
Well, if I go home, I'm going back.

01:22:52.781 --> 01:22:56.911
You know, my whole family's in the Army,
so it's almost the same thing.

01:22:59.755 --> 01:23:02.315
Well, see you guys.

01:23:11.600 --> 01:23:16.162
So, uh, you sure you don't want me
to drive you over to Randy's?

01:23:16.238 --> 01:23:18.900
No, I gotta do this by myself.

01:23:18.974 --> 01:23:20.202
Thanks.

01:23:20.275 --> 01:23:22.209
I'll take a taxi.

01:23:22.277 --> 01:23:24.268
Well, if you need anything,

01:23:24.346 --> 01:23:26.075
you give me a call.

01:23:26.148 --> 01:23:27.706
All right?

01:23:29.918 --> 01:23:33.251
I'm real sorry about that guitar.

01:23:33.322 --> 01:23:34.880
Forget it.

01:23:36.491 --> 01:23:38.322
You bring it to them.

01:23:40.362 --> 01:23:42.125
They're gonna love you.

01:23:52.674 --> 01:23:56.940
...worried about blowing up
some abandoned Iraqi tanks

01:23:57.012 --> 01:23:58.604
and other personnel carriers...

01:23:58.680 --> 01:23:59.612
What'll it be?

01:23:59.681 --> 01:24:02.809
Can I get a shot of tequila?

01:24:02.884 --> 01:24:07.082
Suddenly, out of an alleyway, wham!

01:24:07.155 --> 01:24:10.682
There comes an RPG
and missiles from the air.

01:24:10.759 --> 01:24:12.989
We have been trying
to get a live report...

01:24:13.061 --> 01:24:14.926
Can you make that a double?

01:24:41.223 --> 01:24:42.781
- Yes?
- Hi.

01:24:42.858 --> 01:24:45.986
I'm Colee Dunn.

01:24:46.061 --> 01:24:47.961
I was a friend of Randy's.

01:24:48.029 --> 01:24:50.896
We served together and...

01:24:50.966 --> 01:24:52.991
this is his guitar.

01:24:57.806 --> 01:24:59.273
Well, come in.

01:24:59.341 --> 01:25:01.605
And these flowers are for you, too.

01:25:04.312 --> 01:25:06.177
Thank you.

01:25:06.248 --> 01:25:08.648
We love flowers.

01:25:11.453 --> 01:25:13.944
Here we are.

01:25:14.022 --> 01:25:17.822
You know, you have
such a beautiful home.

01:25:17.893 --> 01:25:19.258
Thanks.

01:25:21.797 --> 01:25:22.764
I guess you didn't...

01:25:22.831 --> 01:25:26.096
you didn't really need the flowers.

01:25:26.168 --> 01:25:29.501
Well, we're always happy for more.

01:25:29.571 --> 01:25:31.937
We have a flower
wholesaling business, so...

01:25:32.007 --> 01:25:34.703
Randy probably told you that.

01:25:34.776 --> 01:25:36.266
Of course, he never liked working there.

01:25:36.344 --> 01:25:38.403
You know boys.

01:25:38.480 --> 01:25:42.883
Always trying to prove they're men.

01:25:42.951 --> 01:25:44.418
I guess working in a flower shop

01:25:44.486 --> 01:25:48.252
didn't quite go with that.

01:25:48.323 --> 01:25:49.950
I must say, I didn't even know

01:25:50.025 --> 01:25:52.493
that Randy played the guitar.

01:25:54.129 --> 01:25:56.757
I thought that...

01:25:56.832 --> 01:25:59.198
I thought that
maybe you gave it to him.

01:26:03.305 --> 01:26:05.034
It wasn't in your family?

01:26:05.106 --> 01:26:06.164
No.

01:26:06.241 --> 01:26:09.608
Our family was never too musical.

01:26:09.678 --> 01:26:13.170
So I don't know where he would have
gotten such a nice guitar.

01:26:16.451 --> 01:26:18.612
That's funny.

01:26:42.944 --> 01:26:44.434
How are you doing today, sir?

01:26:46.114 --> 01:26:47.911
I'll know in about 30 minutes.

01:26:50.252 --> 01:26:52.311
Never too old to sign up.

01:26:52.387 --> 01:26:55.356
You ever think about it?

01:26:55.423 --> 01:26:57.516
I just got out.

01:26:57.592 --> 01:26:59.321
That'd be the best time to get back in.

01:27:00.428 --> 01:27:02.089
Yeah.

01:27:10.005 --> 01:27:11.563
There you go, sweetie.

01:27:13.842 --> 01:27:15.332
<i>Your attention, please.</i>

01:27:15.410 --> 01:27:17.776
<i>Air Canada Flight 63 for Vancouver</i>

01:27:17.846 --> 01:27:20.576
<i>will begin boarding
in approximately 45 minutes</i>

01:27:20.649 --> 01:27:22.776
<i>from Gate C29.</i>

01:27:35.530 --> 01:27:36.622
Can I help you?

01:27:36.698 --> 01:27:37.892
- No, no, no.
- No?

01:27:37.966 --> 01:27:39.160
- You sure?
- Yes.

01:27:39.234 --> 01:27:43.295
Just tell us some more
stories about Randy.

01:27:44.472 --> 01:27:46.440
Okay...

01:27:48.043 --> 01:27:51.012
All right, I'm gonna get that.
Tom, that toast is burning.

01:27:59.220 --> 01:28:02.087
Shannon, this is Colee.

01:28:02.157 --> 01:28:03.852
Colee served with Randy.

01:28:03.925 --> 01:28:06.285
Hi.

01:28:06.361 --> 01:28:09.728
And this is little Jessie.

01:28:09.798 --> 01:28:12.460
He looks just like
his daddy, don't you think?

01:28:12.534 --> 01:28:14.058
He's got Randy's eyes.

01:28:14.135 --> 01:28:17.036
But he's got a bald spot just like you.

01:28:18.139 --> 01:28:20.437
Give me that baby.

01:28:20.508 --> 01:28:23.136
Stop it.

01:28:24.245 --> 01:28:26.805
That's my boy. Yeah.

01:28:41.129 --> 01:28:42.756
How you doing?

01:28:44.499 --> 01:28:45.761
I'm good.

01:28:45.834 --> 01:28:48.564
I'm sorry, Colee.

01:28:48.637 --> 01:28:50.901
You didn't know about Shannon, did ya?

01:28:50.972 --> 01:28:54.135
Yeah, I knew.

01:28:54.209 --> 01:28:55.471
I knew about that.

01:28:55.543 --> 01:28:58.307
He's a damn fool, Randy.

01:28:58.380 --> 01:29:00.041
He never slept with the girl but once.

01:29:00.115 --> 01:29:01.639
He barely knew her.

01:29:01.716 --> 01:29:04.116
But she got pregnant.

01:29:04.185 --> 01:29:07.518
Then he disappeared
and, of course, we felt responsible.

01:29:07.589 --> 01:29:09.147
She was gonna have a baby.

01:29:14.162 --> 01:29:16.892
It doesn't change
whatever you had with Randy.

01:29:16.965 --> 01:29:19.092
Hope you know that.

01:29:25.507 --> 01:29:29.807
<i>This is the final call for Air Canada
Flight 63 to Vancouver.</i>

01:30:29.270 --> 01:30:32.103
He's looking at me to see
if it's okay to eat them.

01:30:32.173 --> 01:30:33.800
- Yes, you may eat them.
- You go right ahead.

01:30:33.875 --> 01:30:35.172
That's delicious.

01:30:38.947 --> 01:30:40.437
Hey, Colee.

01:30:40.515 --> 01:30:43.951
I just want to say

01:30:44.018 --> 01:30:47.920
that Jeanie and I
have talked about this,

01:30:47.989 --> 01:30:51.220
and seeing that you're
kind of out of touch

01:30:51.292 --> 01:30:53.760
with your own family,

01:30:53.828 --> 01:30:58.128
well, we want you to know that...

01:30:58.199 --> 01:30:59.461
that you're welcome to stay here

01:30:59.534 --> 01:31:00.865
for the rest of your leave.

01:31:00.935 --> 01:31:02.459
Really?

01:31:09.711 --> 01:31:11.440
Wow, that's...

01:31:14.983 --> 01:31:16.541
That's so nice.

01:31:18.653 --> 01:31:20.553
I have something that I want to say, too.

01:31:27.562 --> 01:31:31.555
Shannon...

01:31:31.633 --> 01:31:33.897
there's a couple things that you should know.

01:31:37.939 --> 01:31:41.932
Randy... he loved you
with all his heart and soul,

01:31:42.010 --> 01:31:45.036
and he talked about you all the time.

01:31:47.816 --> 01:31:51.775
And, you know, he knew
that he had made a big mistake

01:31:51.853 --> 01:31:54.788
and he was gonna make it up to you.

01:31:57.225 --> 01:32:00.922
And, Tom and Jeanie,
he just loved you so much.

01:32:00.995 --> 01:32:02.690
He knew what great parents you were

01:32:02.764 --> 01:32:07.633
and grandparents, too, and...

01:32:07.702 --> 01:32:11.229
and he was just so looking forward
to coming home.

01:32:15.510 --> 01:32:17.671
Ya'll have been so nice to me.

01:32:17.745 --> 01:32:19.007
And I think I should go.

01:32:19.080 --> 01:32:20.911
- No, no, no.
- Yeah, no...

01:32:20.982 --> 01:32:21.914
You can stay, can't ya?

01:32:21.983 --> 01:32:23.450
No, I think I should go.

01:32:26.955 --> 01:32:30.857
And, you know, I was thinking...

01:32:30.925 --> 01:32:33.086
would it be all right if I took that guitar?

01:32:33.161 --> 01:32:35.026
Randy's guitar?

01:32:35.096 --> 01:32:37.496
Is that okay?

01:32:39.601 --> 01:32:41.193
You take it.

01:32:43.104 --> 01:32:45.698
You're welcome to it.

01:32:47.942 --> 01:32:49.773
Thank you.

01:33:25.546 --> 01:33:26.740
Excuse me.

01:33:26.814 --> 01:33:30.113
I have a friend who I think got arrested.

01:33:30.184 --> 01:33:31.151
You just brought him in.

01:33:31.219 --> 01:33:32.743
- What's the name?
- Poole.

01:33:32.820 --> 01:33:33.844
T.K. Poole.

01:33:38.026 --> 01:33:39.926
Yeah, we got him.

01:33:39.994 --> 01:33:41.427
Can I see him?

01:33:41.496 --> 01:33:43.361
He's still being processed.
You're gonna have to wait.

01:33:45.833 --> 01:33:46.925
What'd he do?

01:33:47.001 --> 01:33:48.832
Doesn't say.

01:33:48.903 --> 01:33:51.633
Must have done something.

01:33:56.044 --> 01:33:57.011
Hello?

01:33:57.078 --> 01:33:58.477
Cheaver!

01:33:58.546 --> 01:34:00.446
Guess what. I got the guitar.

01:34:00.515 --> 01:34:02.676
I told you not to worry about that.

01:34:02.750 --> 01:34:05.218
Are you still in Vegas?
Can I come meet you?

01:34:12.093 --> 01:34:14.027
- Hey.
- Hey.

01:34:22.804 --> 01:34:24.294
How is he?

01:34:24.372 --> 01:34:25.805
They won't let me see him.

01:34:25.873 --> 01:34:28.774
Well, what did he do?

01:34:28.843 --> 01:34:30.834
I don't know.

01:34:36.050 --> 01:34:38.450
Sir? When can we see our friend?

01:34:38.519 --> 01:34:40.009
You can't.

01:34:40.088 --> 01:34:42.352
Listen, we gotta see him.

01:34:42.423 --> 01:34:44.118
He's in the Army. We all are.

01:34:44.192 --> 01:34:46.251
And he's home on leave for just 30 days.

01:34:46.327 --> 01:34:48.022
Now you might not know what that's like...

01:34:48.096 --> 01:34:50.724
I know just what that's like.

01:34:50.798 --> 01:34:52.959
I was a Marine in Desert Storm.

01:34:54.635 --> 01:34:56.865
Well, then maybe you can help us out.

01:35:05.847 --> 01:35:08.577
I have my problems
with my approach shot.

01:35:08.649 --> 01:35:10.207
Oh, see, yeah.

01:35:10.284 --> 01:35:12.252
All you gotta do is just shorten up
that back swing,

01:35:12.320 --> 01:35:15.289
and I guarantee
you'll hit the green every time.

01:35:16.991 --> 01:35:18.424
That's it.

01:35:18.493 --> 01:35:19.960
Like, I don't like to brag,

01:35:20.028 --> 01:35:21.325
'cause bragging doesn't come easy to me,

01:35:21.396 --> 01:35:24.888
but, you know, last time I played
Number 4 at Kuwait City,

01:35:24.966 --> 01:35:26.456
I got a hole in one.

01:35:26.534 --> 01:35:28.559
- Aw, come on, you're bullshitting me.
- No. I'm serious.

01:35:28.636 --> 01:35:31.764
And it was amazing because
the ball never even hit the grass.

01:35:31.839 --> 01:35:34.069
It just dropped straight in the hole.

01:35:34.142 --> 01:35:35.473
There was nothing but cup.

01:35:35.543 --> 01:35:37.738
Swear...

01:35:37.812 --> 01:35:39.677
That's amazing.

01:35:39.747 --> 01:35:40.771
Beautiful, beautiful.

01:35:40.848 --> 01:35:41.872
You know these two?

01:35:43.518 --> 01:35:45.281
Yeah. Hey, guys.

01:35:45.353 --> 01:35:46.980
Hi.

01:35:47.055 --> 01:35:48.920
Hey, your friend here is a real hero.

01:35:48.990 --> 01:35:51.151
Yeah, we know, but why is he here?

01:35:51.225 --> 01:35:53.955
He's here because
he served his country honorably

01:35:54.028 --> 01:35:57.293
and then he came back
and took responsibility for a past mistake.

01:35:57.365 --> 01:35:58.662
That's as brave as it gets.

01:35:58.733 --> 01:36:00.598
What's the charge?

01:36:00.668 --> 01:36:01.760
Armed robbery.

01:36:01.836 --> 01:36:02.996
Armed robbery?

01:36:03.071 --> 01:36:04.834
What did he rob?

01:36:04.906 --> 01:36:07.875
You ever heard of a casino
called Lucky Jim's?

01:36:12.447 --> 01:36:14.312
Yeah.

01:36:14.382 --> 01:36:15.815
Yeah, I heard of that.

01:36:15.883 --> 01:36:19.478
So you robbed Lucky Jim's?

01:36:19.554 --> 01:36:22.148
Yeah.

01:36:22.223 --> 01:36:25.818
And couldn't keep it a secret anymore.

01:36:25.893 --> 01:36:28.521
The guilt was just keeping me up at night.

01:36:28.596 --> 01:36:31.121
A guy who can man up
to his past got my respect.

01:36:35.603 --> 01:36:37.662
Could we have a moment alone with him?

01:36:37.738 --> 01:36:39.603
Is that all right with you?

01:36:39.674 --> 01:36:41.164
Yeah.

01:36:46.647 --> 01:36:48.842
Lucky Jim's?

01:36:48.916 --> 01:36:50.315
Why are you doing this?

01:36:50.384 --> 01:36:53.217
Well, like you said,
I gotta do what I gotta do.

01:36:53.287 --> 01:36:55.187
Find a way to stay alive.

01:36:55.256 --> 01:36:57.554
What, to keep from going back?

01:36:57.625 --> 01:36:59.024
Yeah, it's perfect.

01:36:59.093 --> 01:37:01.561
No. You're gonna go to prison.

01:37:01.629 --> 01:37:03.961
Look at me.
Prison's gonna be easy on a guy like me.

01:37:04.031 --> 01:37:06.056
I got it all figured out.

01:37:06.134 --> 01:37:07.533
I can get a college degree in there.

01:37:07.602 --> 01:37:10.503
These guys said I'll be out in 18 months.

01:37:10.571 --> 01:37:12.664
This is the best thing
that ever happened to me.

01:37:12.740 --> 01:37:13.866
You'll be an ex-con.

01:37:13.941 --> 01:37:16.034
- Yeah, but a living ex-con.
- Right.

01:37:16.110 --> 01:37:19.102
T.K., this is crazy.

01:37:19.180 --> 01:37:20.772
Everybody okay in here?

01:37:20.848 --> 01:37:22.543
- Yep.
- Yes.

01:37:22.617 --> 01:37:25.108
You didn't get hit too hard in the head
fighting over there, did ya?

01:37:25.186 --> 01:37:26.312
No, sir. No.

01:37:26.387 --> 01:37:30.448
Well, then you're all very funny.

01:37:30.525 --> 01:37:33.551
So funny you can get your asses
the hell out of here.

01:37:33.628 --> 01:37:37.564
You think I got time to waste,
Mr. Big Shot Hero?

01:37:37.632 --> 01:37:39.532
You rob Lucky Jim's?

01:37:39.600 --> 01:37:40.692
Yes, sir.

01:37:40.768 --> 01:37:42.565
That's interesting.

01:37:42.637 --> 01:37:45.265
'Cause Lucky Jim's
has never been robbed.

01:37:48.476 --> 01:37:50.569
Sure it has.

01:37:50.645 --> 01:37:52.909
I checked all the records.

01:37:52.980 --> 01:37:56.711
And I just got off the phone
with Lucky Jim himself.

01:37:59.320 --> 01:38:00.947
Now come on, get out of here.

01:38:01.022 --> 01:38:02.649
Take a walk.

01:38:13.534 --> 01:38:14.728
T.K., you okay?

01:38:15.736 --> 01:38:17.761
Hey.

01:38:17.838 --> 01:38:19.533
Oh, man.

01:38:19.607 --> 01:38:22.132
I can't believe I almost did that.

01:38:24.812 --> 01:38:25.938
I can't believe I did that.

01:38:26.013 --> 01:38:28.982
Don't worry. We get it.

01:38:32.553 --> 01:38:34.521
I'm sorry, guys.

01:38:34.589 --> 01:38:36.318
- Don't worry about it.
- Nah, I'm real sorry.

01:38:36.390 --> 01:38:38.324
It's okay.

01:38:38.392 --> 01:38:41.122
Now I'm fucked up.

01:38:45.399 --> 01:38:47.697
Wow, it's official.
I'm fucked up.

01:38:49.704 --> 01:38:51.331
Did you guys know how fucked up I was?

01:38:53.708 --> 01:38:56.609
Didn't really show... that much.

01:38:56.677 --> 01:39:00.340
I gotta reevaluate.

01:39:00.414 --> 01:39:01.813
You know what?

01:39:01.882 --> 01:39:03.816
I'm starting to see things
more clearly right now.

01:39:03.884 --> 01:39:05.613
Good.

01:39:05.686 --> 01:39:07.745
Great.

01:39:07.822 --> 01:39:09.312
I realize that...

01:39:13.561 --> 01:39:16.257
I don't know shit, man.

01:39:16.330 --> 01:39:18.321
Fuck.

01:39:20.167 --> 01:39:21.691
I don't know shit.

01:39:23.070 --> 01:39:25.538
You know some things.

01:39:25.606 --> 01:39:26.538
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

01:39:27.608 --> 01:39:29.337
You got the basic skills.

01:39:37.752 --> 01:39:40.448
So how were Randy's parents?

01:39:40.521 --> 01:39:42.216
They were real nice.

01:39:42.290 --> 01:39:43.655
Good, I'm glad.

01:39:43.724 --> 01:39:46.192
And so was Randy's girlfriend
and his baby, too.

01:39:46.260 --> 01:39:47.488
- Oh. God.
- Ouch.

01:39:47.561 --> 01:39:48.653
Yep.

01:39:50.264 --> 01:39:52.960
But look, I got the guitar,

01:39:53.034 --> 01:39:54.865
and, Cheaver, I want you to have it.

01:39:54.935 --> 01:39:57.665
That's real sweet of you,

01:39:57.738 --> 01:40:00.502
but I don't need it.

01:40:01.876 --> 01:40:02.865
I got the money.

01:40:02.943 --> 01:40:04.843
- What?
- How much did you win?

01:40:04.912 --> 01:40:09.349
I didn't win anything.
I didn't even place a bet.

01:40:09.417 --> 01:40:10.543
I reenlisted.

01:40:10.618 --> 01:40:15.085
You what?

01:40:16.624 --> 01:40:18.455
I reenlisted.

01:40:18.526 --> 01:40:20.426
Got a $20,000 signing bonus.

01:40:20.494 --> 01:40:22.758
I'm all set.

01:40:22.830 --> 01:40:24.388
That's insane.

01:40:24.465 --> 01:40:25.898
You're calling me insane?

01:40:25.966 --> 01:40:27.661
Cheaver, I got you the guitar.

01:40:27.735 --> 01:40:29.726
Sell it. Get the money that way.

01:40:29.804 --> 01:40:32.739
You need that guitar
more than I do, Colee.

01:40:32.807 --> 01:40:35.332
No. I got Army money saved up.

01:40:35.409 --> 01:40:37.536
I'm gonna be fine.

01:40:37.611 --> 01:40:39.909
And I'm gonna find my mom
and patch things up,

01:40:39.980 --> 01:40:41.345
so you take it.

01:40:41.415 --> 01:40:43.747
No. I'm going back.

01:40:43.818 --> 01:40:45.285
Recruiter called my home unit.

01:40:45.353 --> 01:40:47.116
They're transferring the paperwork now.

01:40:47.188 --> 01:40:49.679
You can get out of that.

01:40:49.757 --> 01:40:52.089
I don't know that I want to.

01:40:52.159 --> 01:40:54.753
Cheaver, take the guitar.

01:40:54.829 --> 01:40:56.353
Please.

01:40:58.966 --> 01:41:01.059
You take that guitar, Colee.

01:41:02.403 --> 01:41:04.200
It's your guitar.

01:41:04.271 --> 01:41:05.704
Yeah?

01:41:05.773 --> 01:41:08.173
Yeah.

01:41:10.311 --> 01:41:11.369
Thank you.

01:41:11.445 --> 01:41:15.176
No. Thank you.

01:42:01.128 --> 01:42:02.720
Sergeant.

01:42:04.031 --> 01:42:06.431
T.K.

01:42:06.500 --> 01:42:07.467
How are ya?

01:42:07.535 --> 01:42:09.901
Good. Good.

01:42:09.970 --> 01:42:11.665
So you got here.

01:42:13.841 --> 01:42:15.934
Excuse me.

01:42:19.613 --> 01:42:21.308
- Look who it is.
- Hey.

01:42:21.382 --> 01:42:23.714
- How are ya?
- Good. How are you doing?

01:42:23.784 --> 01:42:25.752
- How are you doing?
- How are you doing?

01:42:28.088 --> 01:42:29.055
Where's your guitar?

01:42:29.123 --> 01:42:30.522
Did you sell it?

01:42:30.591 --> 01:42:32.286
Sell it?

01:42:32.359 --> 01:42:34.293
Hell, no. I'm learning how to play it.

01:42:34.361 --> 01:42:36.090
- You're learning to play it?
- Yep.

01:42:36.163 --> 01:42:37.653
All right.

01:42:40.334 --> 01:42:42.894
How's your fiancée?

01:42:42.970 --> 01:42:45.404
She's fine.

01:42:45.473 --> 01:42:47.964
But she's not my fiancée anymore.

01:42:53.047 --> 01:42:54.344
Where are you going?

01:42:54.415 --> 01:42:55.643
I'm going to Diyala.

01:42:55.716 --> 01:42:58.150
- Where are you going?
- Anbar.

01:43:00.120 --> 01:43:01.553
Where are you going?

01:43:01.622 --> 01:43:03.112
Tikrit.

